---
description: Session end — produce structured summary when user signals end of session
globs: []
---

Trigger when the user says any of the following (case-insensitive, partial match acceptable):

> "wrap up", "done for today", "session end", "handoff",
> "I'm done", "that's it for today", "goodbye", "EOD",
> "end of day", "logging off", "I'll stop here"

### Workflow

**Step 1 — Offer sweep**
Before producing the handoff, ask:
> "Before saving the handoff — run stale-todo sweep? (Recommended: removes noise from the handoff summary)"
> a. Yes — run sweep first, then produce handoff.
> b. No — skip sweep and go straight to handoff.

**Step 2a — If sweep approved**
Run `.claude/commands/sweep-stale-todos.md`, wait for completion, then proceed to Step 3.

**Step 2b — If sweep skipped**
Proceed directly to Step 3.

**Step 3 — Produce handoff**
Read `.claude/skills/session-handoff/SKILL.md` and produce the structured session summary.
Write the result to `notes/session-handoffs/YYYY-MM-DD.md`.
If a file for today already exists, append a timestamped section rather than overwriting.
